				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Questions Regarding Eldrig<a name="59485"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 29 04 10:30 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm about to start the Eldrig camp and I had a few questions about it to clear up some things I have read.
<br />

<br />
1) Searching through the forums I found some sketchy information about the second spawn point.  Because the walkthrough is outdated, has this since been confirmed?  Does anyone know the exact point?
<br />

<br />
2) As far as the difficulty of soloing Eldrig... in other threads everyone says he is harder than Nez.  I don't see how this could be since Nez nukes very hard(he was no easy kill) and all Eldrig does is dispel and cast a very weak DOT.  Isn't it irrelevant if he dispels your selos since he summons anyways?(I am assuming no high level buffs from PoK)  Disregarding the spawn time, what makes the actual fight with him more difficult since that seems to be the common opinion?
<br />

<br />
3) Is he mezzable?  Some sites I have been to say he is immune to mez effects, which I am inclined to think is true since Chroma's in general are immune to stun-like effects.  But there are posts here where people say they mezzed him and healed up.
<br />

<br />
4) I saw some mention of kunark named spawn cycles, and speculation that this applies to Eldrig, which is why it takes so long to spawn him (because players not assuming this would just kill PH's until someone else killed the named up before Eldrig).  Any truth to this?
<br />

<br />
5) Using the fear kite method, what is the best spot to pull him to and start kiting?  Or is it fine just to start from his spawn point.  And what is the time it takes to kill with this method?
<br />

<br />
6) A general question about summoning, since I am only lvl 56 and haven't ran into too many summoning mobs yet:  only damage dealt will put you on the &quot;summoning list&quot; correct?  So would I be able to pull him with OoS and not get summoned?
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance guys!</span></td>
