				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Questions Regarding Eldrig<a name="59487"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 29 04 10:56 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>1) I have no first hand knowledge of this, but like you, I've read that it is confirmed... don't really know.
<br />

<br />
2) I think the difficulty may be in the way people go after them. Some people like to pet zerg to wear them down. Charm something and sic it on him/her while you play some chants. When that pet dies, send in another. This tactic is a problem with Eldrig because as soon as you send in your pet, your charm gets dispelled. So you just can't do that. 
<br />

<br />
3) I seem to remember mezzing him once... sorry, kind fuzzy on that. I know he can be pretty resistant. I took him down when I was level 57 and he resisted me a LOT. Fear was resisted a lot too. After I died, I ended up bringing him to a group hunting cleric shards to help me out (I asked them first of course). No shame in asking for a little help!
<br />

<br />
4) Not quite sure I understand your question, but I think I might... <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  There are no other named that pop out of his spawnpoint, and the 3 times that I've seen him he did pop out of that well known spawn point. So, I don't think he has anything to do with the other named in the zone. I can't confirm this though, as I've never looked to see if there were any other named up when Eldrig was up. If there were, then that would probably mean that's the case.
<br />

<br />
5) I personally think the best place to kite in the whole zone, either fear or chant, is near the BW zoneline. You have some open space there, and if you need to grab a pet to help you out, there's plenty nearby. If you try to fear kite him near his spawn point, you will probably run into adds, unless you can keep him running at the wall. Again, this method didn't work for me b/c of resists. Maybe if you OoS him first (I didnt have it yet).
<br />

<br />
6) Yes. And it's not even JUST damage, it's a certain percentage. I can't recall off the top of my head how much though. I always pull with a non-damaging song.</span></td>
