				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Questions Regarding Eldrig<a name="60992"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 8 04 11:45 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Throwing in my 2cp, spent approx 15 hrs there over the weekend, got my Edrig and a guildies too (didn't want to waste the PH once we'd found it).  
<br />

<br />
Both of us 57.  Initially, had a cleric camp the spawn loc, we both ran around Highsunning everything.  Finally found PH, was down near the wizzy port.  About 40 min or so of Highsunning.  Cleric rooted, we zoned to clear aggro, ran back &amp; killed it.
<br />

<br />
PH popped exactly 13 min from the death of the previous one.  He chant kited, I snared and melee'd (Chromo's we fear kited for practice.)  Everything I tried to mezz was unmezzable, but everything was also charmable.  Never had any problem with adds near the camp.  Over the duration of the camp, we picked up 3 shards, finished 2 clerics shard camps (Now have very good faction with the guild's clerics, lol.)
<br />

<br />
As far as Eldrig himself is concerned, both times there was no cleric nearby when he popped.  First time, no problems... I feared, other bard snared, and straight melee.  Took about 7 minutes to kill him.  Chased him most of the way to the OT zone, got him turned back to spawn, and turned again back toward OT, where he died.  Resisted snare and fear enough to break free a couple of times, but no big deal, never got either of us under 95%.
<br />

<br />
Second time, a lot more difficult.  All good till he got near the OT zone (where the adds are), when snare broke and he took off toward the center of the zone.  Chased him down, but couldn't get fear to stick now...  Ended up charming him so the other bard (who needed the guts) could zone.  (Note: Dispell works to clear his dots.)  While towing him (as pet) to zone, had a chromo pop on top of me, so now I re-charmed Eldrig and zoned too.  Came back, charmed Eldrig, and pulled him to the OT zone, where we got a group of shard farmers to help kill him.
<br />

<br />
Total PH's:  Approx 60 (every 15 min, including time to kill)
<br />
Total Eldrig's:  2</span></td>
